        "title": "Useless static keyword in enclosed interface",
        "body": "<p>If you take a look at <code>java.util.concurrent.Flow.Subscriber&lt;T&gt;<\/code> then you will notice that it is a static interface. However, this code works as well:<\/p>\n<pre><code>class MyCls {\n  interface Enclosed {\n  }\n}\n\n// somewhere ...\nMyCls.Enclosed enclosed = // ...\n<\/code><\/pre>\n<p>As per my understanding, an interface can't be bound to an instance. Why is <code>Flow.Subscriber&lt;T&gt;<\/code> a static interface then?<\/p>\n",
        "question_id": 62779626,
